(Abstract ) show
0 598.8 moveto
12 f2
(The process of understanding a source code in a high-level programming language involves complex) show
0 585.7 moveto
12 f2
(computation. Given a piece of legacy code and a library of program plan templates, understanding the) show
0 572.6 moveto
12 f2
(code corresponds to building mappings from parts of the source code to particular program plans.) show
0 559.5 moveto
12 f2
(These mappings could be used to assist an expert in reverse engineering, legacy code, to facilitate) show
0 546.4 moveto
12 f2
(software reuse, or to assist in the translation of the source into another programming language. In this) show
0.9 533.3 moveto
12 f2
(paper we present a model of program understanding using constraint satisfaction. Within this model we) show
0 520.2 moveto
12 f2
(intelligently compose a partial global picture of the source program code by transforming knowledge) show
0 507.1 moveto
12 f2
(about the problem domain and the program itself into sets of constraints. We then systematically study) show
0 494 moveto
12 f2
(different search algorithms and empirically evaluate their performance. One advantage of the constraint) show
0 480.9 moveto
12 f2
(satisfaction model is its generality; many previous attempts in program understanding could now be) show
0 467.8 moveto
12 f2
(cast under the same spectrum of heuristics, and thus be readily compared. Another advantage is the) show
0 454.7 moveto
12 f2
(improvement in search efficiency using various heuristic techniques in constraint satisfaction. ) show
